  <bioghist id="aspace_04a2d9c57938503b44d7e411f8999702">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>Mortar Board is a national senior honor society for women.</p>  </bioghist>
  <prefercite id="aspace_64867da03b39c72f9675ba05d3d61905">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Mortar Board Honor Society records, #37-4-2199. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_f60463e196ac636ef1d92cf7e88b592a">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Early records of the organization.  Includes a copy of a letter from Caroline H. Swartout to Miss Osborn about the society and a typescript four-page history, 1938.  Also a minute book, 1919-1930. Letter and tape recorded reminiscences of Lulu S. Howard and letter from Lois Osborn, both to Marjorie E. Lasko of Ohio State University for a Mortar Board history project, 1984.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_74d43bd77e8c4946c4593e75da6aef6e">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Recent records of the organization include publicity for lectures and other events, project evaluation forms, planning calendars, and Executive Board agendas and meeting minutes.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_813514fcfda24db72bbc2826dad71ac8">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Also: record of activities, yearly report, Cornell Sun articles, minutes, agendas, announcements.</p>  </scopecontent>
